## 1. Skill Extraction Service (M1)

### Overview
The Skill Extraction Service (Module 1) parses resumes in PDF/DOCX format and extracts structured data fields using a Groq-hosted LLM (Llama 3). It produces 10 structured fields per CV: name, email, phone, location, education, experience, courses, projects, skills, and soft_skills.

### Evaluation Setup
- **Dataset:** 10 curated CVs spanning three difficulty levels
  - Clean (cv_001, cv_002): well-formatted, single-column resumes
  - Medium (cv_003, cv_004, cv_005): mixed formatting, some ambiguity
  - Hard (cv_006–cv_010): poor formatting, missing sections, embedded noise
- **Ground Truth:** Human-annotated JSON files in `data/data for evaluation/m1_test_ground_truth.json`
- **Evaluation Scripts:** `evaluate_live.py` (live API calls), `calculate_metrics.py` (offline simulation)
- **Matching Rules:**
  - Scalar fields (name, email, phone, location): exact case-insensitive; null/null = correct
  - List fields (skills, courses, projects): case-insensitive + alias matching (e.g. react ≡ react.js)
  - Education: institution + degree-level required; year off by ±1 = 0.5 credit
  - Experience: title + company match required

