### Schema Consistency
- M1 uses `fullName`, `cleanSkills`, `coursesAndCertifications` internally; these are remapped to `name`, `skills`, `courses` in the output
- Fields phone, location, and soft_skills are not extracted by the LLM schema (by design) — set to null/[] in response

### Key Observations
- **Best field:** name (F1 = 0.90 macro; 1.00 on all non-failed CVs)
- **Weakest field:** education (F1 = 0.70) — multi-entry records cause degree-level and year mismatches
- **Skills extraction** is strong (F1 = 0.875) even on hard/noisy CVs
- **Projects extraction** drops on cv_008 (F1 = 0.33) due to merged project entries in that CV
- **API availability** is the top risk — one Groq timeout caused cv_004 to fail entirely

