### Strengths
- M3 normalization is perfect — P = R = F1 = 1.00; no false positives or false negatives
- Mode A gap analysis is extremely fast — p95 = 15ms, 33x below the 500ms threshold
- M1 null handling is perfect — 0 hallucinations across all null ground-truth fields
- Mode B handles novel titles not in any pre-indexed database with acceptable quality (F1 = 0.689)
- All 20 GradRAG evaluation thresholds passed in a single evaluation run

### Weaknesses and Risk Areas

| Issue                                            | Service | Severity | Recommended Mitigation                               |
|--------------------------------------------------|---------|----------|------------------------------------------------------|
| Education field is weakest (F1 = 0.70)           | M1      | Medium   | Improve education parsing prompt; add year normalization post-processing |
| cv_004 fully failed due to Groq API timeout      | M1      | High     | Increase retry budget; add queue-based fallback with dead-letter logging |
| Mode B latency near limit (4790ms vs 5000ms cap) | GradRAG | Medium   | Cache Adzuna results; reduce Groq prompt token count |
| Biomedical niche has low ChromaDB coverage       | GradRAG | Low      | Add domain-specific role descriptions to dataroles.txt |
| Mode B consistency at 83.3% (LLM variance)       | GradRAG | Low      | Lower Groq temperature; add majority-vote over 3 runs for critical queries |
| Adzuna live data unavailable in this evaluation  | GradRAG | Low      | Configure ADZUNA_APP_ID and ADZUNA_APP_KEY in production .env |

### Recommendations
1. SHORT-TERM: Fix M1 education field — add explicit year-extraction and degree-normalization post-processing to close the F1 gap from 0.70 to 0.85+
2. SHORT-TERM: Add Groq API circuit-breaker in M1 to prevent a single timeout from zeroing out an entire CV submission
3. MEDIUM-TERM: Integrate Adzuna credentials in GradRAG to enrich Mode B evidence and improve RAG relevance above 0.78
4. MEDIUM-TERM: Expand ChromaDB knowledge base with more niche/specialist role descriptions; focus on biomedical and non-standard titles
5. LONG-TERM: Cache Mode B results by job-title hash (TTL = 24h) to reduce repeat-query latency and Groq API costs

